One of Timely Comics' great successes and very popular in his time, the original Human Torch was an android named Jim Hammond who started off as a monster villain-type character but morphed into a true hero in the mold of his contemporary, Captain America. Along with Cap, Namor the Sub-Mariner, and his partner Toro, Hammond was a founding member of The Defenders and was slowly re-introduced into mainstrean Marvel continuity in 1966, and has been featured in a few solo stories since that time.

This pack collects two of those miniseries and the 70th Anniversary Special which features a new story and a reprint of the first solo Torch issue:

-The Saga Of The Original Human Torch 01-04 (1990)
-The Torch 01-08 (2009-2010, Minutemen+DCP)
-Human Torch Comics 70th Anniversary Special 01 (2009) (Minutemen-Sha-Hic!)

This fills a request from KAT. There is no scanner listed on the Saga miniseries. The Torch has the first issue done by Steam-DCP; the rest are all Minutemen scanners with the individual credits listed in the title of the files. The Special is by MM-Sha-Hic!. Thanks to all of those groups for their efforts, please seed and enjoy! :-)
